Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the analysis of signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) outage probabilities, which is a key concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on the performance analysis of device-to-device (D2D)-enabled millimeter wave (mmWave) cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper deals with the analysis of communication performance in mmWave cellular networks, which is a sub-domain of communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper employs stochastic geometry tools to derive the outage probabilities, which is a technique used in systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the analysis of millimeter wave (mmWave) communications, which is a sub-domain of multimedia.
